Author: jmall#4962
Content: I was developing a project on Starknet, I was wondering whether there are any thoughts around how to handle user interaction until something like events arrive?

Author: jmall#4962
Content: So for example, since it takes time right now for txs to reach a pending state on starknet what are everyone's suggestions on how to handle a faster user interaction?

Author: jmall#4962
Content:
The way I am tackling this is by maintaining a local starknet instance (tbh it's just a simple instane of CarriedState) that is in sync with the main contract instance on starknet. This allows me to check locally whether the txs sent by user is valid or not (according to current state) and respond to their request optimistically. After which the tx request is sent to starknet. 

But trying to keep the local contract instance in sync with contract instance on starknet obviously has problems like, local instance can get out of sync if starknet is called directly.

Author: jmall#4962
Content: Plus other problems that any other hosted backend would face

Author: piotr0874
Content:
I've been interested in this space (data sharing / federated learning / privacy-preserving ML) and I wanted to share few things I think are important here:
- Implementing proper incentives for shareholders. Cold start problem tends to be more persistent than it seems.
- Giving shareholders  tools to design proper governance, and helping them understand, measure and adjust platform risk 
- (In case of federated learning)  Implement server-side security. Models shared across the network must be resistant to "brain-drain" and implement differential-privacy.
That being said I don't see anything wrong with this paper. It's just that building infrastructure is just a top of the iceberg - in order to "scale for industry needs" we need to address much broader issues.

Author: 3rty1
Content: what has been the best way to overcome the cold start friction? Say, you are me with a little JS and a little Solidity--where is the best place to put effort into to expand skillset for Starkware? Sure, it would be good to contribute to an existing project but at this level I'd only get in the way.

Author: piotr0874
Content:
What I meant by the cold-start problem is that when building a data-sharing platform you are essentially creating a two-sided marketplace and these are notoriously difficult to bootstrap. 
I'm also looking to get more involved with StarkNet. I'll be looking for any hackathons or OS projects I can put hours in. It's also interesting to see how to improve existing tools for StarkNet development, like that Hardhat plugin that just came out.

Author: t4or
Content:
Hey everyone, just to give some context about our project and our background: 

In 2017 that we first came up with the idea for Game of Blocks. We launched the first version in 2018: we were inspired by well-known board games such as Risk, Catan and Monopoly. Game of Blocks was a multi-player strategy game (browser based) which enables you earn ETH rewards for each game you win! In a way, it was one of the first play to earn game...

Like many we ran into numerous problems on Ethereum (scaling, gas price, ...) and theses problems which really put the brakes on the widescale adoption of the game. That's why we're bullish on Starkware 👀

Author: roboteddy
Content: it's a protocol that lets you prove that you're an individual unique human (useful for democratic DAO voting, quadratic funding, fair airdrops, etc). Thanks for asking 🙂

Author: roboteddy
Content: ultimately will use zk proofs to offer privacy so you can prove that you're *a* human without revealing *which* human you are

Author: martriay
Content: interesting

Author: martriay
Content: how do you prove personhood?

Author: roboteddy
Content: similarly to https://proofofhumanity.id/ — this project is much-inspired by that one. Basically you just include a photo and video of yourself saying something like "I swear I am not already signed up", along with a deposit. Anyone else is free to challenge you as a duplicate, deepfake, etc (and win money if they are right). Challenges are adjudicated by https://kleros.io/. Working on making a smooth UX so people can get verified in under three minutes, and for fees so small they can be subsidized by the protocol

Author: drspacemn#9574
Content:
I am a Rust dev and was debating between Solana and Starkware, but I'm officially taking the Cairo plunge

Project is called `Jibe` Learn 2 Earn:
- donations are made to "Subject" treasuries 
- a "Subject DAO" then votes on the curation of the curriculum/exams
- as curriculum/exams are rolled out users can complete to earn
- users sign passed exams and DAO votes can then be gated by users that have demonstrated competency on-chain
- DAO votes can be gated by other on-chain factors as well(i.e. lifespan of address, # of interactions with various contracts, etc)

Example:
- The Constitution DAO raised $40Million and stumbled into a FDV of $400Million
- Constitution DAO donates 10,000,000 $PEOPLE to a Jibe treasury
- CDAO votes on the content curation team and to distribute 100,000 $PEOPLE/week until curriculum covering the history and pertinence of the US Constitution is complete
- CDAO votes to approve curriculum
- CDAO votes to pay anyone who completes curriculum and passes exam 20,000 $PEOPLE
- Certain CDAO votes are now gated not by # of $PEOPLE, but by DAO members that have demonstrated competency in whatever values the DAO has decided are pertinent

Non-DAO votes(pie in the sky):
- binary questions that are gated by people demonstrating competency on various subjects
- addresses that have demonstrated competency on-chain in "Climatology" can answer the question: "Are humans catalyzing climate change?"
- results are demonstrated with the percentage of respondents for each to give people a basic heuristic of what subject matter experts think

Author: tonysprocket
Content:
Hey everyone here is a joint project from me and @exp.table adding inheritance to starknet contracts https://github.com/exp-table/starknet-inheritance 

This is meant to be run just before compile-time and is completely text based using python regex; in that way it is similar to macro expansion.

As a byproduct we also create a python data structure representation of a starknet contract

It adds the ability to include code like this in your cairo files:
```
@inherits
ERC20
Ownable
My_Other_Contract
end
```

Hi all, I’m Tomek from TokenFlow. 

We are currently working on the StarkTx transaction decoder which is basically a port of EthTx. The project is in beta and you can test it using https://StarkTx.info 

This release:
- decodes only the top-level call of any StarkNet transaction
- supports Goerli testnet and Mainnet
- supports transactions included in the Pending block

Planned functionalities (as soon as the sequencer API makes them available):
- decoding and displaying events
- decoding and displaying internal calls tree

Any feedback is very welcome!

Author: xan#2113
Content:
Hi Everyone...

A small group of us are looking at building a Fixed rate USD loan protocol. The existing money market protocols like Aave do not fully capture the term structure of rates i.e. what is the fixed rate for 3months / 6months / 12months etc. This term structure is effectively the yield/funding curve which is an important primitive in finance.

We have come up with a design which we think addresses the problem. You can find a link here to the litepaper (only 5 papers) which is hosted on google docs: 

https://docs.google.com/document/d/1rrYC32w63FzzV61rJWqqYomEMgfZ3cRR1jOlJmnnxeY/edit?usp=sharing

I'm also happy to send it to you directly as a pdf if you have concerns on the link. We are looking for 2 things:

1) Some criteria feedback on the design - are we missing anything / will this work / why wont it work
2) We looking for people that are passionate about finance / starknet who could help bring this to life

If you interest at all, we would love to chat, you can dm me here on discord or on twitter at Xan_Crypto

Thanks and appreciate any feedback

Author: widroz#7038
Content: Do you know any "practical" way to provide sybil resistance in Cairo? I am interested in quadratic voting and some alternative to a "list" of humans. Thank you!

Author: guthl_starkware
Content: Tokens supply is a good anti sybil

Author: roboteddy
Content: hi! can you tell me more about what you'd like to accomplish? one way to implement quadratic voting is the way it's done in the Proof of Humanity UBI governance contract — they take `votes = sqrt(number of ubi tokens)` and aim to prevent people from spreading their ubi tokens across many accounts by using Proof of Humanity

Author: widroz#7038
Content: To make it short, I am looking for the "most practical" way to develop in this ecosystem a quadratic voting sybil resistance application with Cairo.

Author: roboteddy
Content: Working on that! You're welcome to come help if you'd like https://zorro.xyz

Author: roboteddy
Content: once you have proof of personhood as a primitive, one of the things you can do is implement quadratic voting

Author: roboteddy
Content: (it's important to do it in a way that protects privacy, though, and which lets people have different pseudonyms for different purposes)

Author: Barty | WrapUp#2122
Content:
Hello StarkNet Community 👋

We are introducing WrapUp, a tool that automatically generates short and informative digests for Discord servers. 

The idea behind the tool is to save time as it’s hard to be on top of everything in servers where hundreds of messages are sent every day.

WrapUp scans messages from public server channels and creates easy-to-read digests with the most relevant information using AI.

StarkNet is one of the first Discord servers we have partnered with and we would love to hear feedback from people here  ❤️

WrapUp is currently in Open Beta and you can try it out here https://wrapup.ai

Author: xan#2113
Content:
Hi Everyone...

Just a quick update, CurveZero is a fixed rate loan protocol thats being built on Starknet. We have made great progress over the last 6 months, with the Cairo codebase being 60-70% complete. Like other lend borrow protocols, liquidity providers deposit USDC into the protocol and borrowers can access this money at fixed rates and at any term they choose. Whereas most lend borrow protocols set the rate of interest based on pool sizes and simple formula's, CurveZero instead relies on external pricing oracles to more accurately capture the correct interest rate at any term.

This more efficient pricing mechanism allows for higher utilization and fairer interest rates. The graph below shows the rates that the pricing oracles would provide at different terms, naturally these are constantly changing as the markets move. The pricing oracles use defi / cefi and tradfi data to create this curve. The important thing to note is there is no longer 1 fixed rate for all terms, that's a thing of the past. Borrowers get a fair / efficient market related rate which increases utilization.

If you passionate about defi and starknet, and want to work on some of the most difficult problems in the space, feel free to reach out. CurveZero's twitter and github links below:

https://twitter.com/curve_zero
https://github.com/xan-crypto/CurveZero

Author: swagtimusprime
Content:
Hey everyone!

MatchboxDAO and Topology.gg are excited to announce Matchbox's first release: Solve 2 Mint v1.

**What's Solve 2 Mint?**

Solve 2 Mint v1 is a physics puzzle for curious problem solvers interested in learning Cairo and exploring the StarkNet ecosystem. 

It contains multiple levels which represent different initial conditions.
- Users submit values that correspond to a score.
- Once a solution is found, that address owns the solution!

**How do I play?**

- Register your discord handle through the SNS app here: https://solve2mint-sns.netlify.app/
- Explore the contracts and read the instructions: https://github.com/Matchbox-DAO/fountain/tree/v0.1/examples/puzzle_v1 
- Enter your solution on https://solve2mint.netlify.app/ 🧠 

**What do I get?**

- First eligibility to beta test games developed by Matchbox on StarkNet. 
- A special role in the Matchbox Discord with a fast track to receive a grant for development ideas on Starknet. 💪 
- The top 5 scores for each level will receive a special NFT! 🐹

We are looking to build a community of curious, like-minded problem solvers and developers.

Our goal is to have this community help shape future puzzles and development on the StarkNet ecosystem!

Announcement blog post: https://mirror.xyz/matchboxdao.eth/XDHA0jqmdXvQDd247ebknsFkXGLG4VfSlGbcU2v6B10
Twitter thread: https://twitter.com/matchbox_dao/status/1511309519959334914

Author: Istvan_A_Seres#7492
Content: Hi all! I'd like to create a VRF from the Legendre PRF using STARKs. My goal is to implement an efficient post-quantum VRF using STARKS (if possible). My statement consists of many sparse multivariate quadratic (MQ) polynomials. The PRF evaluator essentially wants to prove that they know the zeros of this MQ system over the STARK prime field. Before I'd invest much time and energy in coding this up in Cairo, I'd like to understand the proof size that I might have. Could anyone give me some hints, and estimates? A toy example of the circuit the PRF evaluator uses can be found here in Figure 4. (https://eprint.iacr.org/2021/182.pdf). The current state-of-the-art PQ-secure VRF has a proof size of 3KB. My understanding of the original zkSTARK paper is that if one has a multiplicative complexity larger than 2^15, then the proof size will be larger than 100KB, see also Figure 3 here https://eprint.iacr.org/2018/046.pd. Thanks in advance for any comments!

Author: Lior Goldberg#6041
Content:
A STARK proof is practically around 50KB-70KB, basically no matter how much computation you prove with it.
The question is why does the proof size matter in your use case. For example, we are using STARKs on Ethereum, so the cost to put a proof on the chain is what matters (this depends on the proof size, but also on other things). However, since we can put almost any amount of computation in one proof, this amortizes across the different programs we run

Author: BearHug#7547
Content:
Hi All! 

I'd like to introduce my project, **Stash**. 

Its a two-parter:  

- **Stash Protocol** - a collection of Starknet smart contracts written in cairo that allows users to securely lock digital assets and tie them to any location in the metaverse (arbitrary string like URL, GPS coordinates, etc). Any user with knowledge of the location and correct set of keys may unlock the stash and claim its contents.
https://github.com/Stash-Ex/stash-protocol

- **Stash Extension** - a browser extension that enables new interactions and engagement with the web. Built on the Stash Protocol, this web extension allows one to stash digital assets on any website as well as discover and claim stashes left by others, in an entirely permissionless manner.
https://github.com/Stash-Ex/stash-extension

Please have a look at the Github repositories for more information. Both the Stash protocol and extension have roadmaps full of features and enhancements supporting new use-cases. There are additional things that need to be built such as backends, dedicated UI, SDKs for game development (AR/VR), and premium features to support a diverse set of users. 
We are looking for anyone that is interested in the project and would like to 🛠️contribute🛠️. Please feel free to DM me or reach out via Github to discuss further.

Follow these instructions to install the Stash Extension and start creating and discovering stashes today! Both the protocol and extension are live on the goerli test net.
👉(https://github.com/Stash-Ex/stash-extension#installation)👈  
 
Any and all feedback is greatly appreciated. Please start a discussion on the relevant project's discussion board, raise an issue, or post a PR and it will be looked at with utmost urgency.

Author: 0x_rstm
Content:
**Hey StarkNet Community,**

We are happy to present our StarkNet project - **__ZK Social Graph__**.

ZK Social Graph is a Web3, Lens Protocol compatible smart, contracts-based social graph for the StarkNet Ecosystem designed to empower creators to own the links between themselves and their community, forming a fully composable, user-owned social graph. The protocol is built from the ground up with modularity in mind, allowing new features to be added while ensuring immutable user-owned content and social relationships.

Our goal is to build  StarkNet network based Social Graph and appropriate APIs enhanced with ZK security features, ZK badges, combining ZK-Rollup scalability and L2 transaction speed.

Next steps: Social Graph core features development, security and privacy R&D.

Happy to meet you in Starknet.cc 🥳 🇫🇷 

**Contact us:**
✨ Twitter: https://twitter.com/ZKGraph
✨ GitLab Repo: https://gitlab.com/zk-graph
✨ Email: partners@zkgraph.xyz

Author: MrBobbie#6745
Content:
Hello 👋
I'm currently building a project called KAMEN 👀

KAMEN is a blockchain-based Party-to-Earn mobile app where festival-goers own a NFT mask 👺

We aims to reward festival-goers through a loyalty system represented by the evolution of NFT masks. Depending on the rarity and level of the NFT mask, its holder is eligible for two types of rewards:

  - Digital Rewards & Physical Rewards

Each NFT mask is equipped with an experience bar and attributes, which provides specific advantages during festival events. 

We want to develop the first web3 festival community, where owner of a NFT mask becomes a KAMEN loyal ambassador and is rewarded with unique advantages during festival events. So, you can see these NFT masks as social tokens 🔗

If you are interested in this project and are looking to join a team, do not hesitate to contact me by PM 👥

Content:
Hey guys, We have submitted our project - **Comoco** (https://comoco.xyz) and now waiting for the final deployment approval. Let me briefly introduce our project here.

**Comoco** is building a new on-chain infrastructure(Comoco Licensor) and utilities(Comoco Sculptor, Lens & Marketplace) for NFT licensing. Our mission is providing the go-to solution for NFT licensing, utilities and trading on L1&L2, with higher flexibility and lower cost than Layer 1 solutions.

To provide the next gen NFT/IP infrastructure and utilities, Comoco are building:

> **1.Comoco Licensor **is built on StarkNet in form of a serial new Layer 2 protocols for NFT, which support NFT licensing and trading on both L1 and L2.

> **2. Comoco Sculptor **is transforming 2D profile pictures to 3D avatars which are minted as derived NFTs with Comoco Licensor protocol. It enables your 2D NFTs fully animatable and usable in video meetings and more!

> **3. Comoco Lens **is the utility application and showcase to use the 3D avatars for video calls, recording, AR/VR, games and metaverse.

> **4. Comoco Marketplace** is the first marketplace based on Comoco Licensor protocols and introducing ‘NFT Series’ format, which includes original NFT, derived NFT, leasing and sub-licensing trading in the same IP series.

> **5. Comoco Crew** is our first NFT collection of animated 3D avatars with full-body rigging and usable in online meetings & more!

Our twitter: https://twitter.com/comocolabs

So excited to meet you guys in StarkNet!!!

Author: filfjord
Content:
Hey StarkNet team! 

I am from the Fjord Foundry team (We were previously known as Copper Launch). I'd love to chat with you about what we are building and to see how we can support you via Liquidity Bootstrapping Pools (LBPs).

We’ve hosted 100’s of new projects on our platform, which have generated over $750m in liquidity while supporting over $1.5 billion in volume. Our platform has been built to ensure that liquidity generation events are fair, open and transparent meaning that launch events are not impacted by whales, sniper bots and bad actors. This ensures that your project is more sustainable and has true community members invested, allowing you to build an army of ambassadors to supercharge your growth. 

Please let us know if you're up to learning more via a deck or a call as the use cases for Liquidity Bootstrapping Pools don’t end at liquidity generation events which we’d love to explore further with you (e.g. Protocol Owned Liquidity). 

Shout out if you have any questions and thanks for taking the time to read this message. 

Best Regards,

Fil - Business Development at Fjord

Author: priestinprada
Content:
Hey guys, just wanted to introduce https://www.dfns.co/ here as we are currently working on integrating Stark so that buidlers here can forget about the security part and focus on buidling their products. We will also be present at the upcoming Sessions in Tel Aviv.
 
Our product is a wallet infrastructure that allows you (through API) to easily deploy bank-grade wallets seamlessly behind your own platform. We separate security and control of the private key as two different concepts, each private key is generated in 7 pieces spread across different regions of the world and never touched by anyone. The control part is then distributed to the client or end user, either through a JWT or biometrics - meaning users can literally be their own keys (fingerprint or face scan natively on their registered devices - natural 2FA without seed phrases or passwords). 

Some bullet points:
* Deploy your own wallets seamlessly, either full custody or non-custodial without any exposure to private keys, no need for users to remember seed phrases or passwords.
* Granular policy engine to decide who can do what with which assets, with whose approval, to protect yourself and your users from FTX-style internal fraud.
* Scalable to billions of wallets. 
* Works with practically speaking any blockchain and smart contract on the lower level of the API (if you can provide a hash) for advanced interactions
* We're well-funded, impressive team like ex-CISO from Bitgo, CEO, CTO with decades in banks, some of the most cited cryptographers in the world, just to mention a few (feel free to review the competence on Linkedin) 

If you have a project on Stark or in general and want to test out buidling with us, feel free to ping me here. I'm very keen to connect with you personally as I see Stark as a high priority for us.

Nore
Co-founder @ dfns.co

Author: enochstarksport
Content:

Author: unstopmabel
Content:
Gm everyone,
I’m Mabel, marketing from Desig, a blockchain-agnostic multisig solution, enhancing a Trustless ecosystem with multi-fa & social recovery. we’re interested in deploying on Starknet (expected this June) so I thought I should introduce ourselves and discuss potential support with everyone here. 

We are only at the start of 2023 now, and the Web3 market already lost over 180 million dollars over 155 hacks. This situation is why we decided to build **Desig Protocol - a blockchain-agnostic multisig solution.**

Desig divides the master key into shares and gives each signer a share to keep. When someone proposes a transaction, each signer will use their key shares to approve or reject. If Desig collects enough approvals, the key shares will be combined into a valid master key. This way, even if one signer’s key share is compromised, the attacker won't be able to recreate the whole master key. Signers can also be added or removed easily. **The key shares are automatically sent to all members added, so no time is wasted**

There are no differences between Desig’s combined signature and other single-key wallet’s master key signatures. Since all DApps are designed to be compatible with standard single-key wallets, naturally, **Desig is compatible with all DApps.
**
By applying TSS off-chain, Desig is smart contract-less, so there is no point in failure to exploit, and **no fee is charged** in the process. Due to its blockchain-agnostic nature, **Desig is naturally scalable**. It doesn’t rely on smart contracts, which means no devs are required to bridge Desig to any new chain.

To learn more about Desig and what services we may bring, follow our socials: https://link3.to/desiglabs

Let me know if you are interested so we can discuss it. Thank you

Author: williamfu#9792
Content:
Shares are written into smart contracts based on this algorithm. When all 1 billion pieces are minted, users can continue to purchase and use domain name services, but they cannot mint NGT.

About Promotion
Promoters get 10% of their promoters' minting shares, and community leaders get 10% of community members' minting shares.
Users must purchase a domain name in order to become a promoter, otherwise the corresponding address is invalid.

About The Community Leader
In order to facilitate project promotion, community attributes can also be used for subsequent social projects and game projects. For example, the community leader can broadcast messages to community members, and in games, members of the community need to compete for internal community rankings and cooperate. To compete with other communities and other scenarios, so the concept of community and community leader was established.
To become a community leader, the address must first be a valid address (that is, the address that has purchased the domain name), and second, you need to spend 0.01ETH to become the leader (10% to the promoter, 10% to the original community leader).
After becoming a community leader, all invited members belong to the community and enjoy the treatment of 10% of the minting shares of community members.

About The Future
As the community grows, social applications or gamefi will be developed based on the attributes of the community, and all routes will be determined by the community.

Author: ctuannincog
Content:
Hey nice to meet you, this is Ctuann Incog, an Ambassador representing SPACE ID. We are reaching out to introduce you to an exciting development in our ecosystem. We are proud to announce the launch of the SPACE ID 3.0 toolkit, designed to empower projects and ecosystems to launch their own Top-Level Domains (TLDs).

Our toolkit is designed for ease of use, so all details can be tailored to your preferences. This includes domain length, pre-registration rules, domain registration prices, and more.
Furthermore, your domains will have the opportunity to be listed on the SPACE ID 3.0 domain marketplace. This provides your users with a one-stop platform to manage and trade your domains seamlessly.

If the prospect of a branded domain aligns with your roadmap and goals, we are excited to explore potential collaboration possibilities.
Are you interested in launching your own customized domain with SPACE ID? happy to connect you with official team.
